\section{Introduction}
If you are already familiar with \LaTeX{}, then the
LAMUPHYS style file should not give you any major difficulties.
This style file will change the layout to the required style
(it will for instance  define the layout of \verb|\section|).
We had to invent some extra commands,
which are not provided by \LaTeX{} (e.g.\
\verb|\institute|)
We urge you to read
this entire documentation thoroughly. It contains many suggestions
on how to use our commands properly; thus  your paper
will be formatted exactly to Springer standard.
For the input of the references at the end of your contribution,
please follow our instructions given in Sect.\,\ref{refer}
References.

The majority of these hints are not specific for Lamusphys; they may
improve your use of \LaTeX{} in general.
Furthermore, the documentation provides suggestions about the proper
editing and use
of the input files (capitalization, abbreviation etc.) (see
Sect.\,\ref{refedit} How to Edit Your Input File).
